    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_226384729" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/226384729" />
    <a title="reading is my hustle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2069203-reading-is-my-hustle"><img alt="reading is my hustle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1482541792p2/2069203.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/226384729?book_show_action=true">Oct 22, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="reading is my hustle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="reading is my hustle" href="/user/show/2069203-reading-is-my-hustle">reading is my hustle</a>
      </span>

          added it



          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">NO ONE</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2069203-reading-is-my-hustle?shelf=children-middle-reader">children-middle-reader</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer226384729" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5987091558871159541">Poor Miggery Sow; named after a pig, motherless, traded for peanuts, abused, and later described as lazy and fat. Crikey. Also, the author&apos;s penchant for describing things to the <i>Reader</i> drove me bananas. Despereaux actually has a small part considering the continuous horrors of the story: evil rats, ambivalent family members, the Queen&apos;s death, and the no soup decree.</span>
  <span id="freeText5987091558871159541" style="display:none">Poor Miggery Sow; named after a pig, motherless, traded for peanuts, abused, and later described as lazy and fat. Crikey. Also, the author's penchant for describing things to the <i>Reader</i> drove me bananas. Despereaux actually has a small part considering the continuous horrors of the story: evil rats, ambivalent family members, the Queen's death, and the no soup decree.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5987091558871159541" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


